column5: On my way home from work I am listening to the radio and the weatherman says a low of 13 degrees, cloudy and no rain.  Wow! That is pretty warm for this time of year. I immediately pull over to the side of the road  and text Jaydub to see if he is up for some fishing after 8 pm. I went night fishing by myself last Monday nad although I marked loads of fish I managed to only catch 2 good size rock bass. Losts of fish chase but not many commit to the bite.  Quite odd. Anyway, we are on the water no more that 3 minutes and I have a good bite.  I manage to get it to the boat but it jumps and hits the boat and gets off.  It was a good smallie but I did not land it.  Fishing tonight was slow but with the weather being perfect it was still fun. Managed a couple rock bass, perch and some smallies.  Jaydub with a little smallie    Cudz with a nice  big smallie
Nice smallies!I dont think I have ever caught a bass after Thanksgiving weekend! I've been missing out!
My favourite time to catch big smallies.
Yer getting shifty there Chris.Fishing in the dark and no back ground shots.LOL  Nice fish.
Woo! Nice fish! Are you fishing shallower or deeper at night compared to fishing in the day?
good for you guys! never would enter my mind to night fish this time of year
Nothing like mild weather and night fishing!!!
Smae depth, same spots, different bait.
